WEBVTT

00:02.102 --> 00:05.731
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>With gas prices so high, I try not to drive too much.</i>

00:05.839 --> 00:09.570
<i>But when Catalina is so late for work</i>
<i>she's gonna have to change in the car...</i>

00:09.676 --> 00:11.871
<i>it's hard to say no.</i>

00:14.280 --> 00:17.511
Can you drive a little faster?
It's disabled discount day at work...

00:17.617 --> 00:19.585
and the last girl there
gets stuck with Jed.

00:19.686 --> 00:23.417
He's paralyzed from the waist down,
so you never know if you're doing a good job.

00:23.523 --> 00:26.424
Sorry. The engine starts coughin'
if I go over 40.

00:26.526 --> 00:29.689
I think it has something to do with Randy
spittin' his gum in the gas tank.

00:29.796 --> 00:32.390
I told him bubbles wouldn't come out
of the exhaust, but...

00:32.499 --> 00:34.899
sometimes he has to not see things
to believe 'em.

00:38.138 --> 00:40.436
- Is that a hot tub?
- <i>[Earl Narrating] A used hot tub...</i>

00:40.540 --> 00:44.271
<i>laying on the side of the road may not seem</i>
<i>like somethin'to be excited about...</i>

00:44.377 --> 00:46.777
<i>but there was someone on my list</i>
<i>I owed one to.</i>

00:46.880 --> 00:50.509
<i>Number 72- costJoy a hot tub.</i>

00:56.122 --> 01:00.286
Hey, baby.
Wakey, wakey, hands on snakey?

01:00.393 --> 01:04.056
No morning bang today.
Got a job doin' some spokesmodeling...

01:04.164 --> 01:06.132
down at the Camden
Barbecue and Hot Tub Convention.

01:06.232 --> 01:08.166
Barbe-Tub-a-Con is today?

01:08.268 --> 01:10.429
- Mm-hmm.
- <i>Well, how 'bout a quick one before you go?</i>

01:10.537 --> 01:14.735
You know I can't resist you when your hair's
all classy and up high like that.

01:14.841 --> 01:19.039
I know. When I see myself lookin' this good,
I get horny too.

01:19.145 --> 01:21.113
But I don't wanna be late.

01:21.214 --> 01:24.581
- Did I tell you they're payin' me
with a free hot tub?
- Seriously?

01:24.684 --> 01:26.914
Yep.
So just hold on to your stiffy...

01:27.020 --> 01:30.421
and when I get back, we'll fill that thing up
and do it fishy-style.

01:33.560 --> 01:35.528
<i>[Explosion]</i>

01:39.399 --> 01:42.163
Randy, come in here!
We look like cartoons!

01:43.269 --> 01:45.829
<i>My name is Earl.</i>

01:49.008 --> 01:51.602
<i>[Earl Narrating] Catalina was nice enough</i>
<i>to help me with a list item-</i>

01:51.711 --> 01:53.338
<i>gettin'a hot tub forJoy.</i>

01:53.446 --> 01:55.437
All right.
Let's try liftin' it again.

01:55.548 --> 01:58.483
<i>This time I'll try not to fart,</i>
<i>and you make sure your top doesn't fall off.</i>

01:58.585 --> 02:01.713
- [Sighs]
- Ready? Go!

02:01.821 --> 02:05.848
- [Both Grunting]
- Hey! Does anybody knock around here anymore?

02:05.959 --> 02:08.894
Sorry.
We didn't know somebody lived here.

02:08.995 --> 02:11.555
It's an upside-down hot tub
layin' on the side of the road.

02:11.664 --> 02:13.564
Of course somebody's livin' in here.

02:14.968 --> 02:16.833
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>Homeless Joe drove a hard bargain.</i>

02:16.936 --> 02:20.201
<i>He traded the hot tub to us</i>
<i>for a bar of deodorant that he promptly ate.</i>

02:20.306 --> 02:23.400
<i>It was the most exciting thing</i>
<i>to come through the trailer park...</i>

02:23.510 --> 02:27.378
<i>since Mr. Henson tried</i>
<i>to teach his pet monkey to drive stick.</i>

02:27.480 --> 02:29.710
[Children Screaming, Chattering]

02:32.585 --> 02:35.383
Sweet babyJesus.

02:48.268 --> 02:51.396
Mm-mmm.

02:51.504 --> 02:54.166
My whole body's relaxed.

02:54.274 --> 02:59.268
Earl, for the first time ever, you have satisfied me
in a way Darnell never could.

02:59.379 --> 03:02.906
- Go, Earl.
- Guess that means I can cross you off my list.

03:03.016 --> 03:05.985
For sure.
And the timin' is perfect.

03:06.085 --> 03:09.384
I've been havin' to soak my ingrown toenail
in an old Cool Whip container.

03:09.489 --> 03:13.550
<i>Which means Mr. Turtle</i>
<i>gets his swimming pool back. He'll be thrilled.</i>

03:13.660 --> 03:15.685
He can't really stretch out
in the Country Crock tub.

03:15.795 --> 03:20.960
Darnell, get in here. There's a bubble jet
in a place I know you're gonna like.

03:21.067 --> 03:24.332
<i>No, thanks.</i>
<i>I boil animals to death all day long.</i>

03:24.437 --> 03:27.702
If I get in there, God may strike me down
just for the irony of it.

03:27.807 --> 03:31.868
My Uncle Thoroughgood, the fisherman,
choked to death at a sushi restaurant.

03:31.978 --> 03:35.106
Big man's got a sense of humor.

03:40.253 --> 03:43.689
<i>## [Women Vocalizing]</i>

03:43.790 --> 03:47.487
<i>[Earl Narrating]Joy loved her hot tub so much,</i>
<i>she swore she'd never leave it.</i>

03:47.594 --> 03:51.758
<i>And, unlike most ofher promises,</i>
<i>she had already kept this one for 24 hours.</i>

03:51.864 --> 03:55.322
- Baby, you sat in that thing all night.
You ever comin' out?
- <i>## [Continues]</i>

03:55.435 --> 03:58.871
- <i>[Man] # Rock lobster#</i>
- I expect around noon
I'm gonna need to buy another 40.

03:58.972 --> 04:01.736
Unless you wanna try sendin' Dodge
to the liquor store with a note again.

04:01.841 --> 04:06.141
Well, you wanna put these on?
Eugenia says the loud music is makin' her baby cry.

04:06.246 --> 04:08.840
I already put my top back on.
Now you want me to wear headphones?

04:08.948 --> 04:11.109
<i>Besides, I don't care</i>
<i>what these neighbors think.</i>

04:11.217 --> 04:14.948
She's the dumb-ass that sold her Pontiac
to pay for the in vitro!

04:15.054 --> 04:16.954
Now she's livin' with the consequences!

04:17.055 --> 04:21.083
<i>You don't hear me complainin'about</i>
<i>how loud that baby's dialysis machine is.</i>

04:21.194 --> 04:23.958
I mean, how many signs do you need
that somethin' ain't meant to be?

04:24.063 --> 04:26.531
I wish you could see
your foot from up here.

04:26.633 --> 04:31.036
<i>The way the light is hittin'the water,</i>
<i>it makes it look like you've got a giant toe.</i>

04:31.137 --> 04:33.970
No, I can see it from here.
[Chuckles] That is funny.

04:34.073 --> 04:36.598
<i>Hey, watch this:</i>

04:36.709 --> 04:39.507
Big toe, regular-

04:39.612 --> 04:43.742
[Both Screaming]

04:43.983 --> 04:46.645
Well, looks like your toe's infected.

04:46.753 --> 04:48.983
So, what, drink a little cranberry juice?

04:49.088 --> 04:52.649
Mrs. Turner, you have a very contagious,
flesh-eating staph infection.

04:52.759 --> 04:55.853
- What?
- Oh, God. I helped you squeeze your flip-flop on.

04:55.962 --> 04:57.520
How the hell did I get that?

04:57.630 --> 05:00.690
Darnell, if this is some kind
of mad crab disease, I'm gonna kill you.

05:00.800 --> 05:03.462
[Doctor] It's not shellfish related.
I've only seen one case of this in Camden.

05:03.569 --> 05:05.730
It was in a homeless man.

05:05.838 --> 05:09.672
The closest I ever come to the homeless
is buyin' those videos where they fight.

05:09.776 --> 05:13.234
I mean, I like to be charitable,
but I don't wanna just hand 'em the money.

05:13.346 --> 05:15.940
<i>Well, the patient</i>
<i>was a gentleman named Joe...</i>

05:16.049 --> 05:18.415
and he lives out on Route 4
in an old hot tub.

05:20.653 --> 05:23.918
Earl, you son of a bitch.

05:24.023 --> 05:27.857
I'm sorry. I didn't know he was infected.
He seemed like he was into hygiene.

05:27.960 --> 05:29.894
He had a soup can
full of toothbrushes.

05:29.996 --> 05:32.328
But, to be fair,
it was also full of soup.

05:32.432 --> 05:34.593
Look what you did.

05:34.701 --> 05:38.102
- [All] Oh!
- Hell, yeah, "Oh."

05:38.204 --> 05:43.141
Wow. Looks like one of them fancy hot dogs
that plumps in the micro oven. [Sniffing]

05:45.745 --> 05:49.408
You are payin' for my doctor bills,
my pedicure bills and my pill bills.

05:49.515 --> 05:53.246
And no generics either. I want top-shelf meds
like the kind that celebrities O.D. On.

05:53.353 --> 05:56.948
Listen, Joy. Whatever you need, l-I'll do.
Maybe I can come over and-

05:57.056 --> 06:00.890
No, no, no, no, no. You stay the hell away from me.
All I wanna see is your money.

06:00.993 --> 06:03.621
Someone spill milk on the floor?

06:04.731 --> 06:08.189
[Clicks Tongue]
Oh, man! Popped again.

06:08.301 --> 06:10.201
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>Darnell had spent time...</i>

06:10.303 --> 06:12.203
<i>workin'with something</i>
<i>he called "bio weaponry"...</i>

06:12.305 --> 06:14.239
<i>so he knew to take infection seriously.</i>

06:14.340 --> 06:16.501
Can I come in now?

06:18.010 --> 06:20.706
Okay. Ready.

06:23.483 --> 06:25.610
What the hell is all this?

06:25.718 --> 06:29.984
You keep to the foil. The boys, myself
and Mr. Turtle will walk on the regular carpet.

06:30.089 --> 06:32.557
Well, did you have to put it
shiny-side up?

06:32.658 --> 06:35.456
Now I gotta wear my underwear
when the boys are home.

06:41.134 --> 06:43.864
Man, what a day.

06:43.970 --> 06:47.667
I've been lookin' forward to-
to getting into bed and...

06:47.774 --> 06:51.574
forgettin' about this stupid foot
for the next 14 hours.

06:51.677 --> 06:53.645
[Sighs]

06:55.415 --> 06:57.679
What the hell?

06:57.784 --> 07:02.346
It gets chilly in here.
Plus, one of us has to stay alive for the kids.

07:02.455 --> 07:04.923
[Exhales]

07:05.024 --> 07:08.653
[Sports Announcer Chattering On TV]

07:08.761 --> 07:09.762
[Sighs]

07:09.762 --> 07:10.660
[Sighs]

07:10.763 --> 07:12.663
You happy?
Put a bag on it...

07:12.765 --> 07:15.666
so now you don't have to worry
about anybody else catching this.

07:15.768 --> 07:20.102
Yeah, 'cause what germ could make it past
a produce bag and electrical tape?

07:22.308 --> 07:25.607
- You're uncomfortable
even touchin' me, aren't you?
- No.

07:25.711 --> 07:27.611
No.

07:27.713 --> 07:30.546
No.
N- N-

07:31.951 --> 07:34.181
You know what?
I'm gonna go make us some iced tea.

07:34.287 --> 07:36.255
[Pats Leg]

07:40.927 --> 07:42.827
<i>[Cookware Clattering Quietly]</i>

07:42.929 --> 07:48.299
<i>[Clattering Continues]</i>

07:48.401 --> 07:50.301
What are you doin' in there?

07:51.838 --> 07:55.865
- Are you boilin' your clothes?
- I'm makin' iced tea.

07:55.975 --> 07:58.569
Lord love a duck, Darnell.

07:58.678 --> 08:02.045
I'm wearin' a bag.
I'm walkin' on foil.

08:02.148 --> 08:05.515
I'm glazed up in Purell
like a damn Christmas ham.

08:05.618 --> 08:09.486
What do I have to do to not feel like
a filthy leper in my own house?

08:16.062 --> 08:18.826
Bring me Earl Hickey!

08:22.401 --> 08:25.700
Not too shabby.
It's like you're livin' in a snow globe...

08:25.805 --> 08:27.898
but in the summer
'cause... there's no snow.

08:28.007 --> 08:32.034
Which is good because-
[Imitates Shivering]

08:32.144 --> 08:36.171
Darnell, since I'm kinda stuck here, would you
kick Earl in the side of the knee for me?

08:36.282 --> 08:38.216
Listen, Joy.
I feel terrible-

08:38.317 --> 08:40.910
- Ow!
- Sorry, Earl.

08:41.020 --> 08:44.820
I got to appease her. She'll break out
of that thing like a tiny pink Hulk.

08:44.924 --> 08:46.949
Anyway, I gotta go to work.

08:47.059 --> 08:49.084
- Bye, baby.
- Bye.

08:57.236 --> 09:00.433
- I feel terrible.
- Stuck in a bubble
with a flesh-eating disease terrible...

09:00.540 --> 09:02.440
or just a little case of the blues?

09:02.542 --> 09:05.511
Well, the second one.
But I'm ready to make it up to you.

09:05.611 --> 09:08.876
- So if there's anything
you can think of that you want-
- Oh, I've been thinkin'.

09:08.981 --> 09:12.041
You're not the only one
that can make a list.

09:12.151 --> 09:15.314
These are the things that I do all week
but can't since I'm stuck in here.

09:15.421 --> 09:18.948
You've deprived me of my freedom, and
more important, you've deprived the world of me.

09:19.058 --> 09:22.459
So, until I'm free, you gotta be me.

09:22.562 --> 09:25.861
<i>[Earl Narrating] I never thought ofJoy</i>
<i>as someone who has a to-do list...</i>

09:25.965 --> 09:28.900
<i>but it turns out</i>
<i>she was a pretty busy lady.</i>

09:29.001 --> 09:33.961
<i>At 3:00 every Tuesday, she'd go buy meat</i>
<i>out of the trunk of some guy's car.</i>

09:34.073 --> 09:36.234
What part of the animal is this?

09:36.342 --> 09:39.175
I don't even know
what animal it's from.

09:39.278 --> 09:41.974
- [Women Chattering]
- <i>[Earl Narrating] On Wednesdays...</i>

09:42.081 --> 09:46.814
<i>she'd spend four hours at the salon</i>
<i>just to catch up on the latest gossip.</i>

09:49.021 --> 09:51.922
[Dryer Whirring]

09:53.993 --> 09:57.292
And I couldn't quite hear this part,
but Fran said her babysitter...

09:57.396 --> 10:00.456
is addicted to "hooch,"
"pooch" or "cooch."

10:00.566 --> 10:06.300
[Laughs] That sitter's a crazy slut,
so it could've been all three.

10:06.405 --> 10:08.305
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>And, always one to hold a grudge...</i>

10:08.407 --> 10:12.036
<i>every Thursday she'd track down</i>
<i>the local ice cream man.</i>

10:12.144 --> 10:14.874
Don't buy ice cream from this man.
He's a cheat.

10:14.981 --> 10:16.881
If you ask for a rocket pop...

10:16.983 --> 10:20.441
he'll charge you for a double rocket pop
and say it's an accident.

10:20.553 --> 10:22.578
It's a scam.

10:22.688 --> 10:25.020
She really does this every week?

10:26.692 --> 10:29.024
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>But it wasn'tjustJoy I learned things about.</i>

10:29.128 --> 10:33.929
<i>Spendin'so much time with the Turners,</i>
<i>I discovered stuff about the whole family...</i>

10:34.033 --> 10:37.469
<i>like the fact</i>
<i>that Darnell gets migraines.</i>

10:37.570 --> 10:42.803
Two boys, a demanding job,
makin' 2.95 an hour-

10:42.908 --> 10:46.571
These are the things that weigh heavily
on the Crabman, Earl.

10:46.679 --> 10:49.739
Earl, I'm done with my shower.
Bring me some fresh clothes and new hair.

10:51.117 --> 10:53.017
Go ahead.

10:53.119 --> 10:56.885
If you don't, and she starts yellin',
all your rubbing is for naught.

11:00.593 --> 11:02.493
<i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>And the most important thing I learned...</i>

11:02.595 --> 11:06.292
<i>was that Dodge and Earl Junior were the ones</i>
<i>with the biggest problem in the family.</i>

11:06.399 --> 11:10.165
Okay, tomorrow the boys get out of school early,
so you need to hang out with 'em.

11:10.269 --> 11:13.761
I usually take 'em to the arcade or somethin',
since they don't have any friends.

11:13.873 --> 11:16.068
No friends? Are you sure?

11:16.175 --> 11:19.110
<i>Yesterday, Dodge said</i>
<i>him and his friend Roger...</i>

11:19.211 --> 11:22.112
played dress-up
and made funny faces at each other.

11:22.214 --> 11:24.739
"Roger" is what he named his wiener.

11:27.453 --> 11:30.149
That's sad that the boys
don't have any friends.

11:30.256 --> 11:33.714
There's a man downstairs
who's friends with lots of young boys.

11:33.826 --> 11:36.192
We should introduce 'em.

11:36.295 --> 11:39.093
I do wish there was somethin'
I could do.

11:39.198 --> 11:42.099
What'd you do that year in junior high
when you couldn't make any friends?

11:42.201 --> 11:45.136
Oh, Mom got me deodorant.
And then I met Bill.

11:45.237 --> 11:49.139
- Bill was imaginary.
- But our friendship was real.

11:49.241 --> 11:53.177
- And didn't Bill eventually move to Canada?
- Ah, it wasn't his fault.

11:53.279 --> 11:55.509
His dad got transferred.

11:55.614 --> 11:59.516
Then his parents got divorced,
and... Bill started drinkin'.

11:59.618 --> 12:02.246
I had to pull myself
out of that situation.

12:04.090 --> 12:07.423
- <i>[School Bell Rings]</i>
- <i>[Earl Narrating]</i>
<i>I went to pick up Dodge and Earl Junior...</i>

12:07.526 --> 12:10.086
<i>prepared to do anything</i>
<i>to help them get friends.</i>

12:10.196 --> 12:14.257
<i>See you at the party. Everyone's gonna be there.</i>
<i>See you at the party.</i>

12:17.169 --> 12:19.069
- What the hell?
- <i>See you at the party.</i>

12:20.172 --> 12:22.299
Wait in the car.
And put this on.

12:22.408 --> 12:25.104
<i>Look. I don't know what's goin'on here...</i>

12:25.211 --> 12:27.611
but if this is just a B.O. Problem,
I've got it covered.

12:27.713 --> 12:31.410
- Excuse me?
- Dodge and EarlJunior
should be able to come to your party.

12:31.517 --> 12:34.782
- Who are you?
- I'm their mother's ex-husband.

12:34.887 --> 12:38.379
Oh, her ex. [Chuckles]
Well, then you know.

12:38.491 --> 12:43.258
I'm Phyllis Woohoo.
We've had some issues with Joy.

12:43.362 --> 12:45.796
<i>[Earl Narrating] Turns out the boys</i>
<i>weren't the problem at all.</i>

12:45.898 --> 12:48.833
Mmm. Damn!
This punch is better than sex.

12:48.934 --> 12:51.596
What's in it, sherbet?
I'm gonna need a cigarette after this.

12:51.704 --> 12:54.537
- I need a cigarette.
- Better than sex.

12:54.640 --> 12:57.370
Damn!

12:57.476 --> 12:59.967
- <i>Over the years, she made quite a name for herself.</i>
- <i># Evil woman #</i>

13:00.079 --> 13:03.048
That's how you get popular. Once your boobies
grow in, that's gonna look good.

13:03.149 --> 13:08.951
- <i># Evil woman #</i>
- Just don't let that ass get any bigger.

13:09.054 --> 13:12.820
<i>[Earl Narrating] And while some parents</i>
<i>wanted to giveJoy a chance to change, she didn't.</i>

13:12.925 --> 13:17.157
<i>Hey, Mom. Check it out. She got these</i>
<i>really cool water balloons that won't pop.</i>

13:17.263 --> 13:21.563
<i>Oh, they'll pop. If they didn't,</i>
<i>you wouldn't have those two playmates there.</i>

13:21.667 --> 13:25.626
They got into my nightstand. You should've
seen 'em playin' with the lubricated ones.

13:25.738 --> 13:29.640
Looked like they were wrestlin' a greased pig.
[Chuckles]

13:29.742 --> 13:33.508
- <i># Evil woman ##</i>
- Those boys are fine. It's Joy that's the problem.

13:33.612 --> 13:36.080
Well, Joy won't be a problem right now.

13:36.182 --> 13:38.707
She's stuck in a bubble
'cause she has a contagious infection.

13:38.818 --> 13:41.048
About time she got a real disease.

13:41.153 --> 13:43.917
She comes down with cancer
every time we need parents for a field trip.

13:44.023 --> 13:47.186
The first couple of times,
we raised money for her.

13:47.293 --> 13:50.660
Makes you feel any better,
I think she bought cigarettes with that money.

13:53.199 --> 13:57.397
Listen. As-As long as Joy's out of the picture,
here's directions for Dennis's party.

13:57.503 --> 14:02.372
Well, this sounds fantastic. And I'll still
put the deodorant on 'em just in case.

14:02.474 --> 14:05.932
Uh, you're not gonna tellJoy
what I said about her, are you?

14:06.045 --> 14:11.176
You see this? She pierced it with a kebab
after I complained the steak was too dry.

14:11.283 --> 14:14.446
I wore a hoop for a while,
but it made me a little too cocky.

14:14.553 --> 14:17.113
Anyway, I've learned
to keep my mouth shut.

14:21.260 --> 14:25.993
I got your shoes fixed. The repair guy said
to tell you to quit kickin' so many things.

14:26.098 --> 14:29.226
Yes! MyJessica Simpsons.

14:29.335 --> 14:33.066
You see what you're missin'?
You would look so good in these.

14:33.172 --> 14:38.701
<i>That's right, foot. You think about that</i>
<i>the next time you wanna get infected.</i>

14:38.811 --> 14:42.303
- Where are the boys?
- At the park for Dennis's birthday party.

14:42.414 --> 14:44.814
- Dennis who? Dennis Woohoo?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

14:44.917 --> 14:49.877
I think we were wrong about how unpopular
the boys are. They've got friends.

14:49.989 --> 14:53.948
Earl, I know my kids. They never get invited
to anything. This's gotta be a prank.

14:54.059 --> 14:57.654
<i>You know, you invite some loser to your party,</i>
<i>then tie him up, throw dog poo on him?</i>

